Since the invention of the first car by Carl Benz, Mercedes-Benz engineers have been constantly reinventing it, and for over 125 years Mercedes has been improving its cars and adapting them to the changing reality. Mercedes' technological innovations, from the end of the nineteenth century to the present day, are proving themselves again and again and are later adopted by the entire automotive world.
More about technology and innovation at Mercedes-Benz >

Mercedes sees the safety of passengers and users as a top value, and this perception has led to many innovations and breakthroughs in the field of safety, which were first implemented in Mercedes cars and later became the standard in the automotive industry. Among Mercedes' innovations in safety that have become standard in the automotive industry are the first patent for a car airbag (1971), a wheel locking system when braking ABS (1978), and the ESP stability control system invented by Mercedes in 1995. Mercedes continues to lead innovation in the field Safety with systems such as PRE-SAFE, DISTRONIC-PLUS and ATTENTION ASSIST that are currently incorporated under the overall safety concept known as INTELLIGENT DRIVE.

The qualities that Mercedes embodies in its name - luxury, a combination of art and engineering, innovation and timeliness - can be exploited in the expression Mercedes Style that goes beyond the automotive field. Mercedes' style is expressed in different ways and in a variety of areas that Mercedes sponsors such as International International Fashion Week, St.Moritz Art Series and many others.

The legacy of Mercedes-Benz spans over 125 years in which the company has established its position as one of the leading car manufacturers in the world. Mercedes-Benz has played a key role in the history of the automotive industry and has been and still is a pioneer in the fields of technology, safety, design, motor sports and sustainability.
More about the heritage of Mercedes-Benz >

Mercedes Benz Israel was founded by Colmobil in 1963, and was the first importer of luxury cars in Israel. Mercedes Benz Israel is part of Colmobil, which was founded in 1936 and is owned by the Harlap family. The Colmobil Group is the leading car importer in Israel of both private vehicles and commercial vehicles, trucks and buses to Israel.
